VL—ON THE NATURE OF THE POUND on BALANCE

WHoso you are who wonder that the vast heavenly bodies still endure, hung round about the lofty circle of the firmament, and that no decay creeps in upon their mighty mass, hearken‚ that you may wonder yet the more. First-beginnings of utmost fineness and which baffle our sight, are in these great bodies: they hold close together, closely linked in a group of tiny atoms3 but in these tiny atoms is a solid particle which cannot be parted. Hence comes it that their strength and power endure, and that these motions are not overcome by any lapse of time. We may compare things human with divine.
